    "summary": "The desire to understand how things work, along with a curious attitude towards the world, deeply\nbelong to my person, and here lies the primary reason why I attended a PhD course.\nSuch an aspect of my character has guided my life all along; actually, it has been the main\nmotivation for abandoning the high-school classical studies and choosing, instead, the engineering\ncourse.\nAt the university my curiosity turned into commitment to study. I got fascinated and became a\npassionate student.\nAfter the B.Sc., the M.Sc. and the Ph.D. held in 2013, I became a researcher of the Occupational Safety Research Group at the Politecnico di Torino.\n\nAfter 2-years as consultant in Occupational Safety, now I am assistant professor in the chair of Maintenance Engineering within the department of Design, Production and Management of the University of Twente (UT) in the Netherlands. \nMy expertise and research interests lay on Maintenance engineering, Risk Analysis, Antifragility and Resilience Paradigm and the Application of new technologies to Maintenance and Safety topics. \nAt the University of Twente I am the coordinator of the Maintenance Engineering and Operations specialization in Mechanical Engineering Master course. \n\n",
